// A REAL .almd program with an EFFECT CALL (println), so the capability witness
// is derived from real source: the print reaches Stdout. The string `s` is a
// LIVE heap value (borrowed by the print, dropped at scope end) — its ownership
// witness `id` is re-verified by the proven checker. Because `main` declares NO
// capability, the cap witness `|0` is REJECTED: the sandbox promise catches an
// undeclared host effect in real source.
fn main() -> Unit = {
  var s = "hello"
  println(s)
}
